Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of computational linguistics methods to analyze the authorship of Moliere's plays, which suggests that it belongs to the natural language processing (NLP) subfield of computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on analyzing the language and writing style of Moliere and other playwrights of his time, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning algorithms and state-of-the-art attribution methods, which suggests that it may also belong to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of computational methods to analyze language patterns and structures, which could fall under the subfields of deep learning (cs.DL) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
